    "encrypted": "false",
    "long_instructions": "A student is exploring software engineering careers and wants to understand how much salaries vary across cities.\r\n\r\n✅ <strong>TO DO:</strong> In <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Salary.java</code>, write the <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">getDeviation()</code> method. This method should:\r\n\r\n1. Take 5 individual salary values as <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">int</code> parameters.\r\n\r\n2. Calculate the average of the 5 salaries.\r\n\r\n3. Calculate the variance by averaging the squared difference of each salary from the mean.\r\n\r\n4. Return the square root of the variance using <code>Math.sqrt()</code>.\r\n\r\n<div style=\"background-color: #E0D1EC; border: 1px solid #9660bf; border-radius: 5px; font-size: 1.1em; padding: 15px; margin-bottom: 10px;\">\r\n💡 <strong>TIP:</strong> Use <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Math.pow(salary - average, 2)</code> and <code style=\"background-color: #ececec; color: black; font-weight: bold;\">Math.sqrt(...)</code> in your formula.\r\n</div>\r\n",
